    <title>Preferences - Server Settings</title>
    <p>
        The following image displays the Server Settings preferences dialog:
    </p>
    
    <figure>
        <desc>The Server Settings preferences dialog</desc>
        <media type="image" src="Images/preferences-server-settings.png"/>
    </figure>
    
    <p>This dialog allows you to further control the server.</p>
    
    <p>The following options are available:</p>
    <list>
        <title>Crossfade:</title>
        <item><p>Enable crossfade - This sets, whether crossfading is enabled or not.</p></item>
        <item><p>fade time (s) - This sets, how many seconds the songs should blend together on song change.</p></item>
    </list>
    
    <list>
        <title>Output Devices:</title>
        <item><p>This lists all available output devices, which are configured on the server. To enable / disable output devices, check or uncheck the box in the "Enabled" column.</p></item>
    </list>    
    
    <note><p>You can also switch between output devices in the "Server" menu of GMPC's main window or by key combinations.</p></note>
    
    <note><p>MPD not only offers local playback, but also has great streaming support, e.g. over http. Those "output devices" will be shown here as well.</p></note>
</page>
